 2372  // This procedure builds the *scope map* for a given function, which maps any given ast::NodeId in
 2373  // the function's AST to the correct DIScope metadata instance.
 2374  //
 2375  // This builder procedure walks the AST in execution order and keeps track of what belongs to which
 2376  // scope, creating DIScope DIEs along the way, and introducing *artificial* lexical scope
 2377  // descriptors where necessary. These artificial scopes allow GDB to correctly handle name
 2378  // shadowing.
 2379  fn populate_scope_map(cx: &CrateContext,
 2380                        arg_pats: &[@ast::Pat],
 2381                        fn_entry_block: &ast::Block,
 2382                        fn_metadata: DISubprogram,
 2383                        scope_map: &mut HashMap<ast::NodeId, DIScope>) {
 2384      let def_map = cx.tcx.def_map;
 2385  
 2386      struct ScopeStackEntry {
 2387          scope_metadata: DIScope,
 2388          ident: Option<ast::Ident>
 2389      }
 2390  
 2391      let mut scope_stack = vec!(ScopeStackEntry { scope_metadata: fn_metadata, ident: None });
 2392  
 2393      // Push argument identifiers onto the stack so arguments integrate nicely with variable
 2394      // shadowing.
 2395      for &arg_pat in arg_pats.iter() {
 2396          pat_util::pat_bindings(def_map, arg_pat, |_, _, _, path_ref| {
 2397              let ident = ast_util::path_to_ident(path_ref);
 2398              scope_stack.push(ScopeStackEntry { scope_metadata: fn_metadata, ident: Some(ident) });
 2399          })
 2400      }
 2401  
 2402      // Clang creates a separate scope for function bodies, so let's do this too
 2403      with_new_scope(cx,
 2404                     fn_entry_block.span,
 2405                     &mut scope_stack,
 2406                     scope_map,
 2407                     |cx, scope_stack, scope_map| {
 2408          walk_block(cx, fn_entry_block, scope_stack, scope_map);
 2409      });
 2410  
 2411      // local helper functions for walking the AST.
 2412      fn with_new_scope(cx: &CrateContext,
 2413                        scope_span: Span,
 2414                        scope_stack: &mut Vec<ScopeStackEntry> ,
 2415                        scope_map: &mut HashMap<ast::NodeId, DIScope>,
 2416                        inner_walk: |&CrateContext,
 2417                                     &mut Vec<ScopeStackEntry> ,
 2418                                     &mut HashMap<ast::NodeId, DIScope>|) {
 2419          // Create a new lexical scope and push it onto the stack
 2420          let loc = cx.sess().codemap().lookup_char_pos(scope_span.lo);
 2421          let file_metadata = file_metadata(cx, loc.file.name);
 2422          let parent_scope = scope_stack.last().unwrap().scope_metadata;
 2423  
 2424          let scope_metadata = unsafe {
 2425              llvm::LLVMDIBuilderCreateLexicalBlock(
 2426                  DIB(cx),
 2427                  parent_scope,
 2428                  file_metadata,
 2429                  loc.line as c_uint,
 2430                  loc.col.to_uint() as c_uint,
 2431                  0)
 2432          };
 2433  
 2434          scope_stack.push(ScopeStackEntry { scope_metadata: scope_metadata, ident: None });
 2435  
 2436          inner_walk(cx, scope_stack, scope_map);
 2437  
 2438          // pop artificial scopes
 2439          while scope_stack.last().unwrap().ident.is_some() {
 2440              scope_stack.pop();
 2441          }
 2442  
 2443          if scope_stack.last().unwrap().scope_metadata != scope_metadata {
 2444              cx.sess().span_bug(scope_span, "debuginfo: Inconsistency in scope management.");
 2445          }
 2446  
 2447          scope_stack.pop();
 2448      }
 2449  
 2450      fn walk_block(cx: &CrateContext,
 2451                    block: &ast::Block,
 2452                    scope_stack: &mut Vec<ScopeStackEntry> ,
 2453                    scope_map: &mut HashMap<ast::NodeId, DIScope>) {
 2454          scope_map.insert(block.id, scope_stack.last().unwrap().scope_metadata);
 2455  
 2456          // The interesting things here are statements and the concluding expression.
 2457          for statement in block.stmts.iter() {
 2458              scope_map.insert(ast_util::stmt_id(*statement),
 2459                               scope_stack.last().unwrap().scope_metadata);
 2460  
 2461              match statement.node {
 2462                  ast::StmtDecl(decl, _) => walk_decl(cx, decl, scope_stack, scope_map),
 2463                  ast::StmtExpr(exp, _) |
 2464                  ast::StmtSemi(exp, _) => walk_expr(cx, exp, scope_stack, scope_map),
 2465                  ast::StmtMac(..) => () // ignore macros (which should be expanded anyway)
 2466              }
 2467          }
 2468  
 2469          for exp in block.expr.iter() {
 2470              walk_expr(cx, *exp, scope_stack, scope_map);
 2471          }
 2472      }
 2473  
 2474      fn walk_decl(cx: &CrateContext,
 2475                   decl: &ast::Decl,
 2476                   scope_stack: &mut Vec<ScopeStackEntry> ,
 2477                   scope_map: &mut HashMap<ast::NodeId, DIScope>) {
 2478          match *decl {
 2479              codemap::Spanned { node: ast::DeclLocal(local), .. } => {
 2480                  scope_map.insert(local.id, scope_stack.last().unwrap().scope_metadata);
 2481  
 2482                  walk_pattern(cx, local.pat, scope_stack, scope_map);
 2483  
 2484                  for exp in local.init.iter() {
 2485                      walk_expr(cx, *exp, scope_stack, scope_map);
 2486                  }
 2487              }
 2488              _ => ()
 2489          }
 2490      }
 2491  
 2492      fn walk_pattern(cx: &CrateContext,
 2493                      pat: @ast::Pat,
 2494                      scope_stack: &mut Vec<ScopeStackEntry> ,
 2495                      scope_map: &mut HashMap<ast::NodeId, DIScope>) {
 2496  
 2497          let def_map = cx.tcx.def_map;
 2498  
 2499          // Unfortunately, we cannot just use pat_util::pat_bindings() or ast_util::walk_pat() here
 2500          // because we have to visit *all* nodes in order to put them into the scope map. The above
 2501          // functions don't do that.
 2502          match pat.node {
 2503              ast::PatIdent(_, ref path_ref, ref sub_pat_opt) => {
 2504  
 2505                  // Check if this is a binding. If so we need to put it on the scope stack and maybe
 2506                  // introduce an articial scope
 2507                  if pat_util::pat_is_binding(def_map, pat) {
 2508  
 2509                      let ident = ast_util::path_to_ident(path_ref);
 2510  
 2511                      // LLVM does not properly generate 'DW_AT_start_scope' fields for variable DIEs.
 2512                      // For this reason we have to introduce an artificial scope at bindings whenever
 2513                      // a variable with the same name is declared in *any* parent scope.
 2514                      //
 2515                      // Otherwise the following error occurs:
 2516                      //
 2517                      // let x = 10;
 2518                      //
 2519                      // do_something(); // 'gdb print x' correctly prints 10
 2520                      //
 2521                      // {
 2522                      //     do_something(); // 'gdb print x' prints 0, because it already reads the
 2523                      //                     // uninitialized 'x' from the next line...
 2524                      //     let x = 100;
 2525                      //     do_something(); // 'gdb print x' correctly prints 100
 2526                      // }
 2527  
 2528                      // Is there already a binding with that name?
 2529                      // N.B.: this comparison must be UNhygienic... because
 2530                      // gdb knows nothing about the context, so any two
 2531                      // variables with the same name will cause the problem.
 2532                      let need_new_scope = scope_stack
 2533                          .iter()
 2534                          .any(|entry| entry.ident.iter().any(|i| i.name == ident.name));
 2535  
 2536                      if need_new_scope {
 2537                          // Create a new lexical scope and push it onto the stack
 2538                          let loc = cx.sess().codemap().lookup_char_pos(pat.span.lo);
 2539                          let file_metadata = file_metadata(cx, loc.file.name);
 2540                          let parent_scope = scope_stack.last().unwrap().scope_metadata;
 2541  
 2542                          let scope_metadata = unsafe {
 2543                              llvm::LLVMDIBuilderCreateLexicalBlock(
 2544                                  DIB(cx),
 2545                                  parent_scope,
 2546                                  file_metadata,
 2547                                  loc.line as c_uint,
 2548                                  loc.col.to_uint() as c_uint,
 2549                                  0)
 2550                          };
 2551  
 2552                          scope_stack.push(ScopeStackEntry {
 2553                              scope_metadata: scope_metadata,
 2554                              ident: Some(ident)
 2555                          });
 2556  
 2557                      } else {
 2558                          // Push a new entry anyway so the name can be found
 2559                          let prev_metadata = scope_stack.last().unwrap().scope_metadata;
 2560                          scope_stack.push(ScopeStackEntry {
 2561                              scope_metadata: prev_metadata,
 2562                              ident: Some(ident)
 2563                          });
 2564                      }
 2565                  }
 2566  
 2567                  scope_map.insert(pat.id, scope_stack.last().unwrap().scope_metadata);
 2568  
 2569                  for &sub_pat in sub_pat_opt.iter() {
 2570                      walk_pattern(cx, sub_pat, scope_stack, scope_map);
 2571                  }
 2572              }
 2573  
 2574              ast::PatWild | ast::PatWildMulti => {
 2575                  scope_map.insert(pat.id, scope_stack.last().unwrap().scope_metadata);
 2576              }
 2577  
 2578              ast::PatEnum(_, ref sub_pats_opt) => {
 2579                  scope_map.insert(pat.id, scope_stack.last().unwrap().scope_metadata);
 2580  
 2581                  for ref sub_pats in sub_pats_opt.iter() {
